GameEasy - Terms of Service & License

Effective Date: December 23, 2024
1. Introduction

By using GameEasy, you agree to abide by the terms outlined in this document. GameEasy is a software program created by Scratch Software. It is provided free of charge and aims to provide users with a privacy-protected experience while allowing them to easily play games.
2. Privacy Protection

GameEasy and Scratch Software collect absolutely 0% of information about its users. No personal data, usage data, or any other form of data collection will occur within the program, regardless of any permissions granted by the user. We refuse to collect any information as privacy is a fundamental global right. The program does not track, store, or share user data, ensuring that everything remains private. This includes no tracking of games played, preferences, or any interaction with the program.
3. No Account Creation & Security

GameEasy does not require users to create an account. This helps protect against potential data breaches and leaks of personal information. The program is designed to function without needing to store sensitive data, reducing the risk of unauthorized access and ensuring your privacy is protected.
4. Free Usage

All features within GameEasy are free to use. There are no paid services, subscriptions, or hidden costs. You are welcome to use the program without any financial obligation. The program will never ask for payment or offer paid content.
5. Game Content Disclaimer

GameEasy has absolutely no involvement with the content of the games that users choose to play using the program. Whether the game contains illegal content, inappropriate material, or anything else, Scratch Software is not responsible in any way for the content or actions of the games. Users are solely responsible for the games they select to play and for ensuring that their use of GameEasy complies with all applicable laws.

    If the games selected by users collect any information about the user, Scratch Software will have no involvement, and the data collection will be solely the responsibility of the game developers.
